Happy Saturday from our 🏕️campsite🏕️to yours!

We’re dry camping this weekend at McCarty Ranch ran by the amazing folks from the St. Lucie County Parks and Rec Department.  This is that campground that we come back to time and time again. With only six primitive sites, plenty of outdoor activities that we enjoy and plenty of availability, McCarty Ranch is a great way to get away from it all.￼

With temperatures in the 90°s and the “real feel” well over 100° coupled with the site being dry, we will be utilizing the standard onboard systems the FLX has to offer. 

We no longer bring, nor own for that matter, a generator thanks to the 320aH battery being fed by twin 190 watt solar panels and a 3k watt inverter. All of the amenities; convection oven, air conditioner, fridge, etc, run effortlessly off these onboard systems making it perfect for these boondocking excursions!

Is the FLX line the best option for towing with an EV? I would answer that with a resounding YES! There’s no getting around the fact that towing a camper with an electric vehicle is going to reduce your range requiring charging stops along the way. With two humans, our pups and diabetic cat in tow, we know that we can comfortably wait in our FLX while our vehicle is charging up. Straight from the factory, the solar fed 320Ah onboard battery feeds a 3,000W inverter that keeps our AC running, our fridge cold and all of the amenities just a flip of a switch away without the need for shore power. We recently added a second 320Ah #Lithionics battery from #Winnebago extending our off grid excursions with less reliance on plugging the camper into our truck to charge it up.

If you’re looking at the Winnebago line and are considering towing with an EV, we have been happily doing so since 2020 and highly recommend this combo. Happy camping everyone!

We have been to a lot of different campgrounds over the years here in Florida. We have been to the Florida Keys to enjoy the crystal clear waters and pristine weather to St. Augustine, the oldest city in the United States for the rich history to name some of the bucket list locations. There are many memorable trips, but this one to central FL to a small campground at Lake Griffin State Park has been 10 years in the making. While there are some unique features of this campground that we enjoyed, from seeing the 400-500 year old live oak, to kayaking Lake Griffin and hiking the trails to see the wildlife (and many banana spiders that will haunt my dreams) the last picture was the reason I had booked this trip.
For the past decade I have not had contact with my father for reasons that seem trivial after all of these years and time for reconciliation was long overdue.

When I knocked on the door and saw him down the hallway the 10 years of emotion washed over me and a weight had been lifted off my shoulders with the long overdue embrace. 

Unbeknownst to me, my half sister and her husband also resided in the area and along with my step mother we all were able to catch up.

It’s been a week since this trip and today, we’re going fishing together. Hug your love ones, bury the hatchet, because we all have a finite time here on this earth. You can’t get the years back, but take advantage of the ones you have left.

In that moment I knew that our weekend budget was blown 😆
Having a great time at the @hunsaderfarms Pumpkin Festival! Plenty of activities from swamp buggy rides, motorcycle stunt shows, pumpkin cannons, bison, ride on trains, vendors galore and more than can be mentioned here, it’s going to be one fun filled weekend. In addition to the awesome candles we picked up from @msjcandleco , Becca even picked up her first pair of customized Hey Dudes (super comfy) from @tommies_hyde !

Firsts, we seem to always remember the firsts.  In the case of our camping kitty Stella we’ve had a lot over the past 16 years.  The first time she slept in the bed with us, the first time she hopped in our laps, the first time she came camping with us.  The most important first was that Stella was and always will be our first pet.  The first one we rescued in NH from the Humane Society. Our first pet as adults. Our first pet as a couple.  What is tough are the lasts. We don’t realize the lasts until after. 

Unfortunately, tomorrow, we will only have memories as our veterinarian is coming to the house later in the afternoon to help Stella cross that rainbow bridge.  We gave this cat a hell of a life, catering to her every need, getting the most ridiculous toys and taking her on some amazing adventures. She became insulin dependent a few years back and she has been our traveling companion ever since.  We have been dreading this day for a while, but knew it was coming.  Between Stella’s age and her diabetes, additional issues have arisen. Her white blood cell count is skyrocketing due to newly formed anemia, her little kitty kidneys are not up to doing the job anymore and she is now having mobility issues that started a few days ago.  The blood work today confirmed our worst fears and our vet agreed that it was time. 

So why share such a difficult event in our lives?  We want our grief to be a reminder that with the busy lives we all have it’s easy to take our pets for granted.  Find time today to take a break from what you’re doing, give your fluffy family members a pet, a treat, a toy… just spoil them a bit for us because we never know when it will be another last and we are left with only memories.

We’ll miss you Stella.

Utilized the full onboard systems of both our Winnebago and our F150 Lightning. With the weather looking like we were going to be able to forego the A/C we were less than conservative with our preparation and brought meals that would require the convection oven. This, coupled with the temperatures a bit higher than anticipated we were draining our 640Ah of batteries quicker than expected. No longer owning a generator, we utilized the truck’s onboard ProPower which provides up to 9.6kW of power to top off our batteries to power through our adventurous weekend. We rode the trails on our mini bike from #Greenworks took some leisurely rides around the grounds on our #Lectric bikes, spent plenty of time on the water in our #Bote and tired out our pups every chance we had. We even successfully played all 18 holes of the disc golf course here at McCarty Ranch. Out of the 6 RV pads here, we were the only ones to utilize the park all weekend. Our trip was made even more special as we had friends that stopped by for some campfire and good conversation. Happy camping everyone!

Happy Saturday, from our 🏕️campsite🏕️to yours! After hopping onto Campendium, we went looking for a new adventure, something we haven’t tried before. We came across a small, county run park that was known for fossil hunting! Having never tried this before we booked our trip, picked up some fossil hunting supplies and are currently enjoying a weekend we won’t soon forget! Since picking up our first Winnebago in 2020, we feel as if a whole new world of activities and adventures have opened up to us! Our favorite part of Winnebago ownership are the memories that these new adventures bring. Happy camping everyone!

🏕️Doing what we love, with who we love🏕️ 

Once again, the FLX’s standard onboard systems were utilized throughout our stay as we had to prioritize charging the vehicle over plugging in the camper with only one 30amp option on our site. The included 320Ah battery, which we recently added a second to bring our storage to 640Ah, easily powered our adventures while we utilized the power pedestal for our vehicle. 

We had a fun filled weekend with family and friends, enjoyed the stillness of the lake, explored the easy walking paths at this campground whose friendly staff keep clean and well maintained making this a great destination for all. 

Happy camping everyone!
